(453, 129, 'first_paragraph', 'Once upon a time in a kingdom far-far-away in the lands of the never-ending spring, a king sat in his golden throne and ruled his kingdom in perfect harmony. A person can feel nothing but exuberance at the sight of the magnificent castle in which the kind and his daughter lived, the majestic atmosphere of the woods spread all around the castle, and last but not least - the overwhelming beauty of the princess.'),
